│ THOUGHT: The crash stems from dereferencing Preheader->getTerminator() when the preheader exists but lacks a    │
│ terminator (or is malformed). To avoid changing CFG behavior and fix the crash robustly, I will insert a local  │
│ guard immediately after obtaining the Preheader: fetch the terminator into a local variable, bail out if it’s   │
│ null, and then use that variable instead of repeated Preheader->getTerminator() calls. This prevents null       │
│ dereference without altering transformations.                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                 │
